.TH MINIOS-KERNEL-MANAGER 1 "August 2025" "MiniOS Linux" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
minios-kernel-manager \- Graphical tool for managing MiniOS kernels
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B minios-kernel-manager
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B minios-kernel-manager
 is a GTK3 graphical utility that provides a user-friendly interface for managing Linux kernels in the MiniOS distribution. It simplifies the process of packaging, installing, activating, and deleting kernels.
.PP
The application provides an easy-to-use GTK3 interface for:
.IP \(bu 2
Visual selection of kernels with a color-coded status: running (red), active for the next boot (green), and available (blue).
.IP \(bu 2
Safe activation logic that protects the running kernel from being deleted or moved, ensuring system stability.
.IP \(bu 2
Selection of kernels from official repositories or local .deb packages.
.IP \(bu 2
Packaging kernels into SquashFS images and storing them in the I/minios/kernels/R repository.
.IP \(bu 2
Deletion of packaged kernels from the repository.
.SH FILES
.TP
.I /minios/kernels/{version}/
Repository for inactive packaged kernels.
.TP
.I /minios/config.conf.d/kernel-manager.conf
Configuration file storing the BACTIVE_KERNELR variable.
.TP
.I /usr/share/applications/minios-kernel-manager.desktop
Desktop entry file.
.TP
.I /usr/share/polkit-1/actions/dev.minios.kernel-manager.policy
PolicyKit policy file for privilege escalation.
